{"body": "I enhanced a test a bit, because this also happens:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nclass User < ActiveRecord::Base\r\n  store :properties, accessors: [:age, :name]\r\nend\r\n\r\nuser = User.create!(age: 21, name: \"foo\")\r\nuser.age = 22\r\nuser.properties_change # => [{:age => 22, :name: \"foo\"}, {:age => 22, :name => \"foo\"}]\r\nuser.name = \"bar\"\r\nuser.properties_change # => [{:age => 22, :name: \"foo\"}, {:age => 22, :name => \"foo\"}]\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat is, it stopped to track even the current state.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/17185244", "created_at": "2013-04-29T18:35:15Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10373#issuecomment-17185244", "updated_at": "2013-04-29T18:35:15Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 10373, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/janko-m/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/janko-m/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/janko-m/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/janko-m", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/janko-m/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/janko-m", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/janko-m/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/376e4eb9dc6c2e33d1330262edc4f109?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F6bebdda390901c2465d9738120c28b49.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/janko-m/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/janko-m/received_events", "gravatar_id": "376e4eb9dc6c2e33d1330262edc4f109", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/janko-m/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "janko-m", "type": "User", "id": 795488, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/janko-m/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237df6abd3543c151008cdf"}, "id": 17185244, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10373"}
